  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Project Engineer",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></u></p><ol><li>Plan, coordinate, and execute ELV system projects in accordance with specifications, schedule, and budget</li><li>Implement, install, test, and commission ELV systems including Nurse Call, CCTV, Access Control, Intercom, PA System, and Structured Cabling</li><li>Coordinate site activities with clients, consultants, main contractors, and subcontractors</li><li>Deploy and supervise technicians to ensure proper installation and workmanship quality</li><li>Monitor site progress and ensure compliance with technical drawings, standards, and safety requirements</li><li>Troubleshoot technical issues and resolve system integration or installation problems</li><li>Prepare and submit project documentation such as method statements, drawings, test reports, and progress updates</li><li>Provide regular project status updates to management and attend site or coordination meetings as required</li></ol><p></p><p><u><strong>Requirements:</strong></u></p><ol><li>Diploma / Degree in Electrical or Electronic Engineering with at least 1 year of relevant ELV working experience</li><li>Experience in ELV system installation, testing, and commissioning</li><li>Knowledge of Nurse Call and ELV systems is highly preferred</li><li>Familiar with AutoCAD drawings and basic documentation work</li><li>Strong interpersonal and communication skills for site and client coordination</li><li>Self-motivated, independent, and able to work under minimal supervision</li></ol><p></p><p><u><strong>Notes about ISPL:</strong></u></p><ul><li>ISPL is an equal opportunities employer.</li><li>See www.ispl.com for more details of the company.</li><li>ISPL is an SME working environment</li><li>Working hours: 5.5 days’ work week</li></ul>",
